UN urged to take measures against U.S. policy of aggression 
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- Genaro Ledesma Izquieta, chairman of the People's Front of Workers, Peasants and Students of Peru, issued a statement on August 1 as regards the answers leader Kim Jong Il gave to questions raised by Itar-Tass.
 His Russia visit proves the good relations between the DPRK and Russia, he said, and went on:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. clamour about "missile threat" from the DPRK is totally baseless and its foreign policy poses a grave threat to the world people. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 His answers to questions raised by Itar-Tass are of epochal significance in awakening the world people to the real threat of the U.S. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Our organization calls on UN to take measures against the policy of aggression pursued by the U.S. under the pretext of "threat from North Korea".

U.S. clamour about "missile threat" from DPRK refuted
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- The United States, driven into a tight corner by a strong domestic and foreign protest against the Missile Defense System (MD), is citing the "missile threat" from the DPRK as a pretext for pushing forward it.
 Commenting on this, Rodong Sinmun today says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The U.S. administration is working hard to attain its criminal aim at any cost at the sacrifice of the DPRK, but such a trick will work on nobody. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is preposterous for the U.S., the root cause of missile threat, to clamour about the non-existent "missile threat" from the DPRK and it is nothing but sophism to cover up its dominationist intention. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 By desperately working to establish the MD the U.S. seeks to have an absolute nuclear edge over other countries and establish its unchallenged domination over the world. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK is compelled to take a countermeasure for self-defence, given that the U.S. pushes forward the MD under the pretext of "threat" from the DPRK. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK makes it clear once again that its missile program is of purely peaceful nature and it threatens nobody. It is our legitimate sovereign right to carry out peaceful missile program. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 It is the DPRK's unshakable stand and will to reciprocate good will and react to a hard line with a super hard line. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 No one has a right to fault the DPRK for it.

15th World Festival of Youth and Students opens
 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; El Djazair, August 8 (KCNA correspondent) -- The 15th World Festival of Youth and Students opened in El Djazair on August 8.
 The festival is being held in the African continent in the first year of the new century under the slogan "Let us wage world-wide struggle against imperialism and for peace, solidarity and development" .&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK delegation of youth and students was the first to enter the place of the opening ceremony, breaking the custom of the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The crowd welcomed with cheers and applause the Korean young men and women marching with the flags bearing portraits of President Kim Il Sung and leader Kim Jong Il in the centre of their ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Members of the delegation danced graceful, rhythmical folk dances. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The secretary general of the general union of Arab students said that the graceful dance rhythm and valiant and militant spirit shown by the DPRK delegation greatly contributed to decorating the beginning of the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He said he was moved to see its vigorous demonstration of national dignity and might with the flags bearing the portraits in its ranks. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Algerian President Abdelaziz Bouteflika in his congratulatory speech said that future belongs to youth and the youth should unite to struggle for freedom and peace. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Meanwhile, the President met with Kim Kyong Ho, secretary of the central committee of the Kim Il Sung Socialist Youth League who is heading the DPRK delegation to the festival. On the occasion the President said that the DPRK delegation showed a very good demonstration at the entrance ceremony for the opening of the festival. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Korean art is on the world-level and the Korean youth is really good, he stressed, adding that the relations between Algeria and the DPRK provided by Kim Il Sung have long traditions. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The Korean national club for the 15th World Festival of Youth and Students opened at the El Djazair palace of culture on August 9. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The DPRK delegation will hold friendship gatherings and exchange of views with delegations of youth and students from different countries and conduct distinctive and colorful activities including book and photo exhibitions and art performances there.

Anecdotes about Kim Il Sung
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pyongyang, August 11 (KCNA) -- It happened when President Kim Il Sung was on a trip to give on-site guidance to mountainous Sakju county.
 Feasting his eyes with deep attention on a maize field from his car running on the steep roadside, he asked the chauffeur to stop the car. He walked into the field and examined maize ears to know if they were ripened and how heavy they were. Holding a handful of earth, he told officials to prospect the area, saying that there might be an apatite deposit for sure, as maize was doing well in the sloping field. Later prospecting officials surveyed the place where the car stopped, confirming the area as an apatite deposit. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 This was how a big apatite mine came into being in the DPRK where apatite was considered as not available before. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 There is another anecdote about him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One summer day in Juche 49 (1960), he happened to meet an angler by the side of the Sunhwa River flowing at the foot of Mangyong Hill. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Praising his angling skill, he asked about his occupation. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Feeling ashamed, the man told the president that he was working as a barber at a school. saying that his job was very good, the president told him how gratifying he would feel to stroke down pupils' hair as a barber as he himself has no time to pat all the pupils on the head. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 He repeatedly asked him to take good care of pupils, the treasure and future of the country. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Another anecdote about him says: &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 One day in Juche 35 (1946), an old man working for a democratic political party visited his office and made a rare request to him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 The man told Kim Il Sung that he married a woman shortly ago only to be "maltreated" as he was old. So he asked the president to help him get some tonics such as wild Insam (Ginseng) and young antlers of the deer. Laughing hearty laugh, the President promised to help him so that his wife might not despise him. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 A year later the 70 years old man became father of a son. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
 Later the president spared time to attend a feast given in celebration of his son's 100 days after birth.
